args:
As the prince and his allies attempt to enter the
Faerie Kingdom at Finlorda's urging, a group of
androids appear and bar the way. Though the
faeries were supposedly using them for
peaceful ends, they attack the prince's group.

After making our way through the Faewood
and over snow-capped mountains, we arrived
at a lake on the summit only to find the path
to the Faerie Kingdom blocked.

Because of Harle's scheming, we were
assailed by dragons and other enemies,
but we fought them—thanks in no small
measure to some great work by Notte.
Afterward, we passed through a route used\nin ancient times and finally found ourselves\nin the Faerie Kingdom.
Guys, if we stay on this path, it's gonna\ntake us right to the dude who's been\ntalking to me this whole time!
What a curious spectacle this is.
Yes, I've never seen houses of such unique\nstyle before—and just look at the vibrant\ncolors of the trees!
I feel fresh, powerful waves of mana\npulsing from the land itself.
That's because the roots of the Sacred Tree\nin the north stretch all the way here.

The faeries know a thing or twenty about
how to handle mana, so they've been
putting it to use in their daily lives for
ages upon ages.

And the adolescent faeries who travel
beyond the kingdom always come back
bearing the knowledge and wisdom
of the wider world.
From that, they've worked out all manner\nof fascinating tricks and ideas that extend\nfar beyond our collective knowledge.
Guess that's why they're so good\nwith the ol' hocus-pocus, yeah?
But hey, where are the faeries, anyway?
Forget faeries—we haven't seen anyone\nor anyTHING since we came over here.
I fear our citizens have been ordered\nto remain in their homes.
You there! Disembodied voice!\nWhat do you mean, they were ＂ordered＂?
This land is the very definition of peaceful,\nso why did you lock your subjects away?
Perhaps it has something to do with us.
Yes, I suspect as much. Now forgive me,\nbut I must implore you to hurry to my\nlocation as quickly as you are able.
Eyes on, everyone! We have company.
I am detecting several unidentified\nsignatures moving to our location.
▷I'm analyzing them now!◁\nThey are presently 30 paces from our\ncurrent position. ...Twenty. ...Ten.
Identity of unknown signatures confirmed.\n▷What the...?!◁
The hell? It's a buncha androids!\nWhat are they doing here?
They are property of the faeries.
Incomprehensible. It is impossible for\nfaeries to be in possession of androids.
▷Laxi's right. We're weapons that were\nmade by humans to defeat dragons.◁
And you faeries are said to be distant\nrelatives OF the dragons, correct?
So how would you even be able to\nacquire human-made androids?
...We found a number them abandoned\non ancient sites of battle and restored\nthem to operation.
We'd hoped to use them for manual labor\nand self-defense purposes.

Comparing present signature to registered
target. Accordance rate: 100 percent.
Confirmed that current signature is a
match for termination target.
No, I'm good. Still, I can't believe\nhow suddenly they attacked!
For machines used in self-defense,\nthey are being quite aggressive!
Picking up additional enemy signatures.\n▷We've got more incoming!◁
Sounds like they ain't gonna let us through\nso easily.
Can't you order these androids\nto stand down, Finlorda?
Forgive me, but at present,\nI am powerless to act.
It would seem our only path forward is\none we must cut ourselves.
Mascula! Laxi! Can't you order these guys\nto knock it off?!
I surmise they are currently being\ncontrolled with a specialized mechanism.\nSeizing command will be difficult.
Nothing for it, then—we'll have to\ndefeat them all and press on!
